text: James McGuinness may refer to: * James Kevin McGuinness (1893–1950), American screenwriter and film produce * James McGuinness (bishop) (1925–2007), Roman Catholic bishop of the Diocese of Nottingham * Martin McGuinness (James Martin Pacelli McGuinness, 1950-2017), Irish Sinn Féin politician and deputy First Minister of Northern Ireland ==See also== * Jim McGuinness (born 1972), Gaelic footballer * Jay McGuiness (born 1990), English singer and member of The Wanted
